{
  "stem": "22869.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bearing in mind, you're talking about people who are normally at this stage of the game not capable of doing anything.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was really a miracle that-- that-- that all of us were not to taken with trucks and dumped into the mass graves and killed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they had a-- a system.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apparently, right now, whoever can still breathe and walk has to try to bury the other one who is already dead.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had different kind of jobs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not all the time where we were together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We tried to, but it wasn't always working out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the-- most of the people at that time, the ones who did not run freely to the electric wires to take their lives-- and that itself took-- took also a certain amount of stamina to do.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But once you gave up-- and we have watched this day in and day out, many, many times.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But everybody-- not everybody is powerful enough or strong enough to-- to end his own life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And remember that most of the people at that time were suffering from diarrhea, and that was probably like, like cholera, like you-- you-- you-- you're undernourished.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You haven't got any vitamins.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You haven't got any minerals in your body.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Your-- your-- your weight is diminished to almost nothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then you develop diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "At that time in Auschwitz, almost everybody had that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So once you had diarrhea, you haven't got the possibility to go to bathrooms, so you do it in your pants.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You're all wet, and the next time an SS man sees you, he knew right away, this is it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then they used to grab you off the walk during-- during the course of walking to work, from work.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
